BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In healthcare IT and business processes, MBR_FNDTN is the baseline or master record that defines a member’s identity and core attributes. It serves as the authoritative source of truth for linking the member to enrollment, claims, providers, and payers.
Transformation Logic:
SELECT DISTINCT
  mf.MBR_SK
FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_base b
join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf on b.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID AND b.CURR_REC_IND='1'
LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.cnty_cd c on b.CDE_COUNTY = c.CNTY_ID AND c.CURR_REC_IND='1'
where mf.CURR_REC_IND='1'

UNION DISTINCT

SELECT DISTINCT
  mf.MBR_SK
FROM (select * from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_multi_address where trim(CDE_ADDR_USAGE) in ('R','M') and CURR_REC_IND='1')a
join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf on a.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.cnty_cd c on a.CDE_COUNTY = c.CNTY_ID AND c.CURR_REC_IND='1'
where mf.CURR_REC_IND='1'

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In healthcare IT and business processes, MBR_FNDTN is the baseline or master record that defines a member’s identity and core attributes. It serves as the authoritative source of truth for linking the member to enrollment, claims, providers, and payers.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: MBR_SK is the surrogate key assigned to a member record in the data warehouse.
Transformation Logic:
with phone_adr As (
  select trb.sak_recip,trb.SAK_CDE_PHONE,trb.NUM_PHONE,trb.SAK_ADD_PHONE,trb.NUM_ADD_PHONE,trb.TENANT_CD,trb.SRC_SYS_CD
  from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_base trb
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_cde_phone cp ON trb.SAK_CDE_PHONE = cp.SAK_CDE_PHONE AND cp.CURR_REC_IND ='1'
  where trb.CURR_REC_IND='1' and trb.SAK_CDE_PHONE != 0
  union distinct
  select distinct
    tma.sak_recip,tma.SAK_CDE_PHONE,tma.NUM_PHONE,tma.SAK_ADD_PHONE,tma.NUM_ADD_PHONE,tma.TENANT_CD,tma.SRC_SYS_CD
  from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_multi_address tma
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_cde_phone cp ON tma.SAK_CDE_PHONE = cp.SAK_CDE_PHONE AND cp.CURR_REC_IND ='1'
  WHERE tma.CURR_REC_IND ='1' AND tma.SAK_CDE_PHONE != 0 and tma.CDE_ADDR_USAGE in ('R','M')
),

cte_mbr_phone as (
  select sak_recip,CDE_PHONE,NUM_PHONE, NUM_ADD_PHONE,TENANT_CD,SRC_SYS_CD
  from (select *, row_number() over (partition by sak_recip, CDE_PHONE, NUM_PHONE order by NUM_PHONE desc) as seq
    from (
      select sak_recip,SAK_CDE_PHONE as CDE_PHONE, NUM_PHONE,'' AS NUM_ADD_PHONE,TENANT_CD,SRC_SYS_CD from phone_adr where NUM_PHONE != ''
      union distinct
      select sak_recip, SAK_ADD_PHONE as CDE_PHONE,'' AS NUM_PHONE, 
			case when SAK_CDE_PHONE = SAK_ADD_PHONE and NUM_PHONE = NUM_ADD_PHONE then '' else NUM_ADD_PHONE
        end as NUM_ADD_PHONE, TENANT_CD, SRC_SYS_CD from phone_adr where NUM_ADD_PHONE != ''
    )
    where (NUM_PHONE != '' or NUM_ADD_PHONE != '') and (NUM_PHONE != NUM_ADD_PHONE)
  ) where seq = 1
)
SELECT DISTINCT
  mf.MBR_SK
FROM cte_mbr_phone AS a
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON a.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID AND mf.CURR_REC_IND='1'

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: This suggests it is a base or foundational table that stores information about recipients — typically meaning patients, members, or beneficiaries in the U.S. healthcare context.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: sak_recip is typically a recipient identifier used to uniquely represent individuals in beneficiary tables.
Transformation Logic:
WITH mbr_fndtn_cte AS (
  select
    SRC_KEY_ID, MBR_SK
  from oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.MBR_FNDTN
  WHERE CURR_REC_IND = '1'
),

t_re_base_cte AS (
  select *
  from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.T_RE_BASE
  where CURR_REC_IND = '1'
),

tmp_ind_dual_elig AS (
  SELECT COND1.sak_recip
  FROM (
    SELECT DISTINCT A.sak_recip
    FROM t_re_base_cte AS A
     JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_hib B																	 -- BRONZE Source Table
      ON A.sak_recip = B.sak_recip
        AND A.ind_active = 'Y' AND B.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
     JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_buy_tbq TBQ                                  -- BRONZE Source Table
      ON A.sak_recip = TBQ.sak_recip
        AND TBQ.ind_applied = 'Y'
        AND TBQ.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
    JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_buy_tbq_pbp PBP                                -- BRONZE Source Table
      ON TBQ.SAK_BUY_TBQ = PBP.SAK_BUY_TBQ
        AND TRIM(CDE_TYPE) = 'P'
        AND CURRENT_DATE() BETWEEN TO_DATE(STRING(PBP.dte_start), 'yyyyMMdd')
        AND TO_DATE(STRING(PBP.dte_end), 'yyyyMMdd')
        AND PBP.CURR_REC_IND = '1'

  ) AS COND1
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT A.sak_recip
    FROM t_re_base_cte AS A
    --JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_elig B                                     -- BRONZE Source Table
    INNER JOIN bronze_t_re_elig AS B
      ON A.sak_recip = B.sak_recip
        AND B.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
    WHERE CURRENT_DATE() BETWEEN TO_DATE(STRING(dte_effective), 'yyyyMMdd')
      AND TO_DATE(STRING(dte_end), 'yyyyMMdd')
  ) AS COND2
    ON COND1.sak_recip = COND2.sak_recip
)

SELECT DISTINCT
  decode(DELG.sak_recip, NULL, 'N', DELG.sak_recip, 'Y') AS DUAL_ELG_IND
FROM
  t_re_base_cte AS b
INNER JOIN mbr_fndtn_cte AS mf ON b.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
LEFT JOIN tmp_ind_dual_elig AS DELG on b.SAK_RECIP = DELG.sak_recip

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In healthcare, enrollment is the process of registering a member into a health insurance plan, Medicaid/Medicare program, or employer-sponsored coverage. The MBR_ENRL_FNDTN entity or table typically serves as the baseline record that defines a member’s enrollment foundation — the core data from which all other enrollment details are derived.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: Surrogate key that uniquely identifies member enrollment key (Lookup) for MEMBER ENROLLMENT DETAIL record from plan foundation
Transformation Logic:
WITH t_re_elig_cte ( select * from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_elig where CURR_REC_IND = '1' ),
t_pub_hlth_pgm_cte AS (SELECT SAK_PUB_HLTH,CDE_PGM_HEALTH, CDE_TYPE_PLAN FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm WHERE CURR_REC_IND = '1')

SELECT DISTINCT
  mef.MBR_ENRL_SK
FROM t_re_elig_cte tre
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_enrl_fndtn mef ON concat(tre.SAK_RECIP,'|', tre.SAK_PGM_ELIG) = mef.MBR_ENRL_KEY_ID
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON tre.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
JOIN t_pub_hlth_pgm_cte ph ON tre.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH AND ph.CDE_TYPE_PLAN = 'BNFT'
JOIN t_pub_hlth_pgm_cte ph1 ON tre.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph1.SAK_PUB_HLTH
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn pf on ph1.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = pf.SRC_KEY_ID AND pf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_elig_stop es ON tre.SAK_ELIG_STOP = es.SAK_ELIG_STOP AND es.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_financial_payer fp on tre.SAK_FIN_PAYER = fp.SAK_FIN_PAYER AND fp.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.fnncl_payr_cd fps on fp.CDE_FIN_PAYER = fps.FNNCL_PAYR_CD AND fps.CURR_REC_IND='1'

Silver Table Description:
Recipient Aid Category Eligibility contains the recipient's aid category eligibility segments. An aid category eligibility segment specifies a period of time that the recipient is eligible for Medicaid coverage in that aid category. Each segment is maintained by an effective date and end date. For each date range, there will be a corresponding aid category that will be used to determine what services are included in the recipient's Medicaid coverage for that period of time.

For further information about how the program code and aid categories are determined and how they relate, refer to the Recipient User Manual.
Silver Attribute Column Definition: Surrogate key that uniquely identifies a MEMBER ENROLLMENT AID CATEGORY record in MEMBER ENROLLMENT AID CATEGORY table.

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In U.S. healthcare, especially Medicaid and other public programs, aid categories (sometimes called “aid codes”) are used to classify members based on their eligibility type. These categories determine what benefits the member receives, how claims are adjudicated, and how reporting is done to CMS or state agencies.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: SAK_PGM_ELIG is the surrogate key field that uniquely identifies a program eligibility record in the aid eligibility table.
Transformation Logic:
WITH t_re_aid_elig_cte AS (
  SELECT * from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_aid_elig where CURR_REC_IND = '1' and TRIM(CDE_STATUS1) != 'H'
),
mbr_fndtn_cte (SELECT * from oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn where CURR_REC_IND = '1')

SELECT DISTINCT
  CAST(SAK_PGM_ELIG AS INTEGER) AS ELG_SEQ
FROM (SELECT * from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_aid_elig where CURR_REC_IND='1' and TRIM(CDE_STATUS1) !='H')ae
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON ae.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID and mf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_cert_agency ca on ae.SAK_CERT_AGENCY = ca.SAK_CERT_AGENCY and ca.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.org_fndtn ofn on ca.CDE_CERT_AGENCY = ofn.SRC_KEY_ID and ofn.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_cde_aid ca on ae.SAK_CDE_AID = ca.SAK_CDE_AID and ca.CURR_REC_IND='1'
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.aid_cd ac on ca.CDE_AID_CATEGORY = ac.AID_CAT_CD and ac.CURR_REC_IND='1'

QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY concat_ws('|',ae.TENANT_CD,ae.SRC_SYS_CD,mf.MBR_SK,ae.SAK_PGM_ELIG,AID_CAT_CD,SRC_EFF_DT,SRC_END_DT)
 ORDER BY ae.DTE_LAST_UPDATE DESC) = 1

Silver Table Description: This table will allow relationships between a recipient and provider for the purposes of care.  The types of information that will be stored on this table are the recipient level of care nursing home information, provider lockin information, hospice information, some provider specific waiver information, and other benefit information that will relate a recipient to a provider.   Note: Managed Care also handles relationships between the recipient and the provider for benefits that the provider is paid for.
Silver Attribute Column Definition: Surrogate key that uniquely identifies a MEMBER ASSIGNED PLAN record in MEMBER ASSIGNED PLAN table.

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In healthcare IT and business processes, MBR_FNDTN is the baseline or master record that defines a member’s identity and core attributes. It serves as the authoritative source of truth for linking the member to enrollment, claims, providers, and payers.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: MBR_SK is the surrogate key  (Lookup from member foundation) assigned to a member record in the data warehouse.
Transformation Logic:
SELECT DISTINCT
  mf.MBR_SK 
FROM
  ( SELECT * from oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_assign_plan where CDE_STATUS <> 'H' and DTE_END >= DTE_EFFECTIVE and CURR_REC_IND = '1') AS ap
	INNER JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn AS mf ON ap.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID and mf.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
	LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn AS pf
  on right(pf.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(pf.PROV_KEY_ID)), 0) - 1) = ap.SAK_PROV_LOC
    and pf.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
	LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm AS ph on ap.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH and ph.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
	LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn AS plnf
  on ph.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = plnf.SRC_KEY_ID and ph.CDE_TYPE_PLAN = 'ASGN' and plnf.CURR_REC_IND = '1'
	QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER ( PARTITION BY ap.SRC_SYS_CD,ap.TENANT_CD,concat_ws('|','MBR_SK',mf.MBR_SK,'PROV_SK',pf.PROV_SK,'PLAN_SK',plnf.PLAN_SK,'SRC_EFF_DT',SRC_EFF_DT)
    ORDER BY ap.DTE_LAST_UPDATE DESC
  ) = 1
Join Column Description:
CDE_STATUS:Represents the current status of the member’s assigned plan record.|DTE_END:DTE_END is the date field that records when a member’s Assigned Plan record change ends (expires).|DTE_EFFECTIVE:DTE_EFFECTIVE is the date field that records when a member’s Assigned Plan become active|CURR_REC_IND:Y/N to indicate whether this is the most current or Active record|SAK_RECIP:sak_recip is typically a recipient identifier used to uniquely represent individuals in beneficiary tables.|SAK_PROV_LOC:SAK_PROV_LOC stands for Surrogate Assignment Key for Provider Location. It is a system-generated unique identifier that represents a specific provider service location within the assignment or provider network context.|SAK_PUB_HLTH:system-assigned surrogate key that uniquely identifies a Public Health Program record associated with a member’s Primary Care Provider (PCP) assignment.|SRC_SYS_CD:Source Code – Identifies the source system from which the record originated in MEMBER ASSIGNED PLAN table.|TENANT_CD:Code representing the customer who owns the given record in MEMBER ASSIGNED PLAN table.|SRC_EFF_DT:Source Effective Date – The date when this record becomes valid in the source system in MEMBER ASSIGNED PLAN table.|DTE_LAST_UPDATE:DTE_LAST_UPDATE is the date field that records when the record was last updated in the system.|SRC_KEY_ID:SRC_KEY_ID is a field that represents the recipient’s identifier or key within a state assistance or Medicaid program in MEMBER FOUNDATION table.CURR_REC_IND:Y/N to indicate whether this is the most current or Active record|MBR_SK:Member Surrogate Key – A unique warehouse-generated key representing the member entity in MEMBER FOUNDATION table.|PROV_KEY_ID:System-assigned surrogate key that uniquely identifies a provider location record in the source system.|CURR_REC_IND:Y/N to indicate whether this is the most current or Active record|PROV_SK:PROV_SK stands for Provider Surrogate Key. It is a system-generated unique identifier for a provider record within the Provider Foundation layer.|SAK_PUB_HLTH:A system-assigned surrogate key that uniquely identifies a Public Health Program record associated with a member’s Primary Care Provider (PCP) assignment.|CURR_REC_IND:Y/N to indicate whether this is the most current or Active record|CDE_PGM_HEALTH:A code representing the Public Health Program within the system. This code identifies the specific health program
|CDE_TYPE_PLAN:CDE_TYPE_PLAN (Code – Type of Plan) is a coded field that identifies the type of health plan a recipient is enrolled in. It ensures standardized plan classification, supports claims adjudication, compliance reporting, and enables analytics on plan participation and outcomes.
|SRC_KEY_ID:Source Key ID – The original identifier (Plan ID) from the Plan table in PLAN FOUNDATION table.|CURR_REC_IND:Y/N to indicate whether this is the most current or Active record|PLAN_SK:system-generated unique identifier used to represent a specific health plan record within the Plan Foundation layer of the data warehouse or master data model

SELECT DISTINCT
CAST(SAK_SHORT AS INTEGER) AS MBR_RNEWL_SEQ
FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_re_member_renewal mr
JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON mr.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
WHERE mr.CURR_REC_IND='1' and b.CURR_REC_IND='1' and mf.CURR_REC_IND='1'

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In healthcare IT and business processes, MBR_FNDTN is the baseline or master record that defines a member’s identity and core attributes. It serves as the authoritative source of truth for linking the member to enrollment, claims, providers, and payers.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: MBR_SK is the surrogate key  (Lookup from member foundation) assigned to a member record in the data warehouse.
Transformation Logic:
with CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp as (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    mf.MBR_SK,
    pf.PLAN_SK,
    ppsl.PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK,
    prf1.PROV_SK,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_EFFECTIVE AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_EFF_DT,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_END AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_END_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_LOCK_IN AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS LOCK_IN_DT,
    pa.CDE_STATUS1 AS STS_CD,
    pa.IND_PRIMARY AS PRI_IND,
    pa.CDE_MC_REGION AS MNGD_CARE_REG_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_START AS MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_STOP AS MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_ADDED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS INSRT_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_PROV_MBR_ADD AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS PROV_MBR_ADD_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_CHANGED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS CHG_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_TERMED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TERM_DT,
    pa.CDE_CALL_METHOD AS CALL_MTHD_CD,
    pa.TENANT_CD,
    pa.SRC_SYS_CD
  FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN pa
  JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON pa.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm ph on pa.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH and ph.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn pf on ph.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = pf.SRC_KEY_ID and pf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pmp_svc_loc psl on pa.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC = psl.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC and psl.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf on right(prf.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = psl.SAK_PROV_LOC and prf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_pcp_svc_loc ppsl on ppsl.PROV_SK = prf.PROV_SK and ppsl.PLAN_SK=pf.PLAN_SK and ppsl.CURR_REC_IND='1' --5155250
  left join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf1 on right(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = pa.SAK_PROV_LOC_MBR and prf1.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  where pa.CURR_REC_IND='1'
)
select
  pa.MBR_SK
from CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp AS pa

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In Medicaid managed care and other health programs, each member (recipient) is typically assigned to a Primary Medical Provider (PMP) who coordinates their care.The T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN table provides the authoritative list of assignment codes, reasons, and rules used when linking recipients to PMPs. It ensures consistency across enrollment, case management, claims adjudication, and compliance reporting.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: DTE_EFFECTIVE is the date field that records when a member’s Primary Medical Provider (PMP) become active
Transformation Logic:
with CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp as (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    mf.MBR_SK,
    pf.PLAN_SK,
    ppsl.PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK,
    prf1.PROV_SK,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_EFFECTIVE AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_EFF_DT,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_END AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_END_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_LOCK_IN AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS LOCK_IN_DT,
    pa.CDE_STATUS1 AS STS_CD,
    pa.IND_PRIMARY AS PRI_IND,
    pa.CDE_MC_REGION AS MNGD_CARE_REG_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_START AS MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_STOP AS MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_ADDED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS INSRT_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_PROV_MBR_ADD AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS PROV_MBR_ADD_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_CHANGED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS CHG_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_TERMED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TERM_DT,
    pa.CDE_CALL_METHOD AS CALL_MTHD_CD,
    pa.TENANT_CD,
    pa.SRC_SYS_CD
  FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN pa
  JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON pa.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm ph on pa.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH and ph.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn pf on ph.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = pf.SRC_KEY_ID and pf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pmp_svc_loc psl on pa.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC = psl.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC and psl.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf on right(prf.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = psl.SAK_PROV_LOC and prf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_pcp_svc_loc ppsl on ppsl.PROV_SK = prf.PROV_SK and ppsl.PLAN_SK=pf.PLAN_SK and ppsl.CURR_REC_IND='1' --5155250
  left join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf1 on right(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = pa.SAK_PROV_LOC_MBR and prf1.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  where pa.CURR_REC_IND='1'
)
select
  pa.SRC_EFF_DT
from CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp AS pa

BRONZE_TABLE_DESCRIPTION: In Medicaid managed care and other health programs, each member (recipient) is typically assigned to a Primary Medical Provider (PMP) who coordinates their care.The T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN table provides the authoritative list of assignment codes, reasons, and rules used when linking recipients to PMPs. It ensures consistency across enrollment, case management, claims adjudication, and compliance reporting.
Bronze_Attribute Column Description: Provider Member Add Date – The date when the provider added the member to their panel or system.
Transformation Logic:
with CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp as (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    mf.MBR_SK,
    pf.PLAN_SK,
    ppsl.PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK,
    prf1.PROV_SK,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_EFFECTIVE AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_EFF_DT,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_END AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_END_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_LOCK_IN AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS LOCK_IN_DT,
    pa.CDE_STATUS1 AS STS_CD,
    pa.IND_PRIMARY AS PRI_IND,
    pa.CDE_MC_REGION AS MNGD_CARE_REG_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_START AS MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_STOP AS MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_ADDED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS INSRT_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_PROV_MBR_ADD AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS PROV_MBR_ADD_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_CHANGED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS CHG_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_TERMED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TERM_DT,
    pa.CDE_CALL_METHOD AS CALL_MTHD_CD,
    pa.TENANT_CD,
    pa.SRC_SYS_CD
  FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN pa
  JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON pa.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm ph on pa.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH and ph.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn pf on ph.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = pf.SRC_KEY_ID and pf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pmp_svc_loc psl on pa.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC = psl.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC and psl.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf on right(prf.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = psl.SAK_PROV_LOC and prf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_pcp_svc_loc ppsl on ppsl.PROV_SK = prf.PROV_SK and ppsl.PLAN_SK=pf.PLAN_SK and ppsl.CURR_REC_IND='1' --5155250
  left join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf1 on right(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = pa.SAK_PROV_LOC_MBR and prf1.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  where pa.CURR_REC_IND='1'
)
select
   pa.PROV_MBR_ADD_DT
from CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp AS pa

Silver Table Description: This describes a recipient's Primary Medical Provider (PMP) assignment. This information is required for a recipient to be linked to a PMP and to participate in a managed care program.
Silver Attribute Column Definition: Call Method Code – Code representing the preferred method of communication (e.g., PHONE, EMAIL, MAIL) in MEMBER ASSIGNED PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIAN table.

Bronze_Attribute Column Description: System Surrogate Key - SSK usually refers in MEMBER ASSIGNED PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIAN to a system-generated unique identifier used to represent an entity.
Transformation Logic:
with CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp as (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    mf.MBR_SK,
    pf.PLAN_SK,
    ppsl.PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK,
    prf1.PROV_SK,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_EFFECTIVE AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_EFF_DT,
    CAST(TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_END AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TIMESTAMP) AS SRC_END_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_LOCK_IN AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS LOCK_IN_DT,
    pa.CDE_STATUS1 AS STS_CD,
    pa.IND_PRIMARY AS PRI_IND,
    pa.CDE_MC_REGION AS MNGD_CARE_REG_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_START AS MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD,
    pa.CDE_RSN_MC_STOP AS MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_ADDED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS INSRT_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_PROV_MBR_ADD AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS PROV_MBR_ADD_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_CHANGED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS CHG_DT,
    TO_DATE(CAST(pa.DTE_TERMED AS STRING), 'yyyyMMdd') AS TERM_DT,
    pa.CDE_CALL_METHOD AS CALL_MTHD_CD,
    pa.TENANT_CD,
    pa.SRC_SYS_CD
  FROM oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.T_RE_PMP_ASSIGN pa
  JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.mbr_fndtn mf ON pa.SAK_RECIP = mf.SRC_KEY_ID
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pub_hlth_pgm ph on pa.SAK_PUB_HLTH = ph.SAK_PUB_HLTH and ph.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT JOIN oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.plan_fndtn pf on ph.CDE_PGM_HEALTH = pf.SRC_KEY_ID and pf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.bronze_dmes_de.t_pmp_svc_loc psl on pa.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC = psl.SAK_PMP_SER_LOC and psl.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf on right(prf.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = psl.SAK_PROV_LOC and prf.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  LEFT join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_pcp_svc_loc ppsl on ppsl.PROV_SK = prf.PROV_SK and ppsl.PLAN_SK=pf.PLAN_SK and ppsl.CURR_REC_IND='1' --5155250
  left join oz_dev.silver_dmes_de.prov_fndtn prf1 on right(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID, nullif(charindex('|', reverse(prf1.PROV_KEY_ID)),0)-1 ) = pa.SAK_PROV_LOC_MBR and prf1.CURR_REC_IND='1'
  where pa.CURR_REC_IND='1'
)
select
   concat_ws('|',pa.TENANT_CD,pa.SRC_SYS_CD,'MBR_SK',pa.MBR_SK,'PROV_SK',pa.PROV_SK,'PLAN_SK',pa.PLAN_SK,'PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK',
    pa.PROV_PCP_SVC_LOC_SK,'SRC_EFF_DT',pa.SRC_EFF_DT,'SRC_END_DT',pa.SRC_END_DT,'STS_CD',pa.STS_CD,'MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD',
    pa.MNGD_CARE_BGN_RSN_CD,'MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD',pa.MNGD_CARE_STOP_RSN_CD,
    'INSRT_DT',pa.INSRT_DT,'CHG_DT',pa.CHG_DT,'TERM_DT',pa.TERM_DT,'LOCK_IN_DT', pa.LOCK_IN_DT,'CALL_MTHD_CD',pa.CALL_MTHD_CD
  ) AS MBR_ASSGN_PCP_SSK
from CTE_mbr_assgn_pcp AS pa
